    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "hey my realtor just mentioned i need to set up an escrow account for this house i'm buying in toronto. i'm kinda confused. whats escrow actually and why do i need it for the closing?",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Escrow, in this context, is a trust account that holds funds for you and the seller until the closing of the transaction. It's a bit like a temporary holding cell for your earnest money deposit, where it's safely kept until the final payment is made. You'll need to set up an escrow account to hold the funds for property taxes and insurance, which are typically paid annually. This way, you can ensure that these ongoing expenses are covered before you take possession of the property. It's a common practice in Toronto, and your realtor is likely recommending it to avoid any last-minute surprises.",
